{{Infobox cycling race report | name = 2007 Vuelta a Venezuela | image = | image_caption = | date = August 27 &ndash; September 9 | series = [[2006–2007 UCI America Tour]] | stages = 14 | distance = 2180 | unit = km | time = 49h 24' 11" | speed = 44.1268 | first = [[César Salazar (cyclist)|César Salazar]] | first_nat = COL | first_team = Lotería del Táchira | first_color = red | second = [[Richard Ochoa]] | second_nat = VEN | second_team = Gobernación Bolivariano | third = [[Tomas Gil]] | third_nat = VEN | third_team = Gobernación Bolivariano | points = [[Gil Cordovés]] | points_nat = CUB | points_team = Alcaldía de Cabimas | mountains = [[César Salazar (cyclist)|César Salazar]] | mountains_nat = COL | mountains_team = Lotería del Táchira | sprints = [[Gil Cordovés]] | sprints_nat = CUB | sprints_team = Alcaldia de Cabimas | youth = [[Jimmy Briceño]] | youth_nat = VEN | youth_team = Gobernación Barinas | team = Lotería del Táchira | previous = [[2006 Vuelta a Venezuela|2006]] | next = [[2008 Vuelta a Venezuela|2008]] }}
The 44th edition of the annual '''[[Vuelta a Venezuela]]''' was held from August 27 to September 9, 2007. The stage race started with an Individual Time Trial (18.8&nbsp;km) in [[Carúpano]], and ended in [[Caracas]].
==Stages==
