{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Bhausaheb Bandodkar Ground | nickname = | country = India | image = | location = [[Panaji]], [[India]] | establishment = 1963 | seating_capacity = 10,000 | end1 = Mandovi River End | end2 = D.B. Bandodkar Road End | club1 = [[Goa cricket team|Goa]] | year1 = 1986&ndash;2006 | date = 29 October | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1167.html Ground profile }}
'''Bhausaheb Bandodkar Ground''' (also known as '''Campal Grounds''' and '''Panjim Gymkhana Grounds''') is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Panaji]], [[Goa]], [[India]]. The first recorded match held on the ground came in 1966 when Gujarat Governor's XI played Maharashtra Governor's XI.<ref>{{cite web |subscription=yes |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1167_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Bhausaheb Bandodkar Ground, Panaji|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 October 2011}}</ref> The first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] to be played there came in the 1986/87 [[Ranji Trophy]] when [[Goa cricket team|Goa]] played [[Tamil Nadu cricket team|Tamil Nadu]]. Between the 1986/87 season and the 2005/06 season, the ground held 26 first-class matches.<ref>{{cite web |subscription=yes |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1167_f.html|title=First-class Matches played on Bhausaheb Bandodkar Ground, Panaji|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 October 2011}}</ref> The first [[List A cricket|List A]] match played there came when Goa played [[Kerala cricket team|Kerala]] in the 1993/94 Ranji Trophy one-day competition. Fifteen further List A matches have been played on the ground, the last of which saw [[Andhra Pradesh cricket team|Andhra Pradesh]] play [[Hyderabad cricket team|Hyderabad]] in the 2004/05 Ranji Trophy one-day competition.<ref>{{cite web |subscription=yes |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1167_a.html|title=List A Matches played on Bhausaheb Bandodkar Ground, Panaji|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=29 October 2011}}</ref>
