The '''Bowling and Cue Sports Federation of the Islamic Republic of Iran''', more commonly known as the '''Iran Bowling and Cue Sports Federation''' ('''IBCSF''' or '''IranBCS''' for short) is the governing body in [[Iran]] of [[bowling]]{{clarify|{{subst|DATE}}|reason=Ten-pin only, or more than one kind? If ten-pin only, link to [[Ten-pin bowling]], not [[Bowling]].|date=October 2011}} and [[cue sports]] (including [[snooker]], [[carom billiards]] and [[Pool (cue sports)|pool]]).  Founded in 2000, the organization was originally known as the '''Iran Bowling and Billiards Federation''' ('''IBBF''').

IBCSF is member of the [[National Olympic Committee of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Iran National Olympic Committee]], and is also the national affiliate of [[Fédération Internationale des Quilleurs]], [[World Tenpin Bowling Association]], the [[Asian Confederation of Billiard Sports]] (regional division of the [[World Confederation of Billiards Sports]]), [[International Billiards and Snooker Federation]] and [[World Pool-Billiard Association]], and [[Asian Pocket Billiard Union]] as the governing body of these sports in Iran.

