{{Orphan|date=December 2012}}

The '''Italian Golf Federation for Disabled''' (FIGD) is an association whose aim is to promote [[golf]] among [[Disabled people|disabled]] players in [[Italy]]. It was established in 1998. FIGD is member of the [[Federazione Italiana Golf]] (Italian Golf Federation), of the [[Comitato Italiano Paralimpico]] (Italian Paralympic Committee) and the [[European Disabled Golf Association]] (EDGA).

