'''Safia Abukar Hussein''' (born 1 January 1981) is a [[sprint (running)|sprint]]er who competed internationally for [[Somalia]].

Hussein was the first [[Somalia|Somali]] female to compete at the Olympics for her country<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/SOM/ Somalia at the Olympics]</ref> when she competed in the [[Athletics at the 2000 Summer Olympics – Women's 400 metres|400 metres]] at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]], she finished her heat in 6th place so not advancing to the next round.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/hu/safia-abukar-hussein-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>

