{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Savannakhet stadium | nickname = | image =[[File:SVK-std-inside3.JPG|300px]]| | location = {{flagicon|Laos}} [[Savannakhet]], [[Laos]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = March 2005 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | Constructor = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | nicknames = | tenants = Savan United | seating_capacity = 15,000 | dimensions = 95 x 60 m }}
The '''Savannakhet stadium''', also known as '''Savannakhet Provincial stadium''', is a multi-purpose stadium in [[Savannakhet]], [[Laos]]. It is used mostly for [[Association football|football]] matches. The stadium is built in 2005 and holds 15,000 people. Since 2006, some matches of the [[Lao League]] have been played there. The stadium is also the home of [[Savannakhet FC]], who will play in the Lao League in one of the following seasons.
