{{refimprove|date=April 2010}} {{more footnotes|date=April 2010}} {{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= Turkish Fencing Federation |abbrev = TFF |sport=[[Fencing]] |category = |jurisdiction = [[Turkey]] |founded = 1923 |aff = [[Fédération Internationale d'Escrime|FIE]] |affdate =1923 |region = [[Confédération Européenne d’Escrime|CEE]] |regionyear =1923 |headquarters = Ulus, [[Ankara]], [[Turkey]] |location = |president = Müminhan Bilgin |chairman = |chiefexec = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = www.eskrim.org.tr |countryflag= Turkey }}
The '''Turkish Fencing Federation''' ({{lang-tr|Türkiye Eskrim Federasyonu}}) is the [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for the sport of [[fencing]] in [[Turkey]]. It was founded in 1923. In 1924, Turkish fencers began to attend the [[Olympic Games]].<ref>[http://www.eskrim.org.tr/Tarihce.asp History of fencing in Turkey]</ref> Every year, fencing tournaments are held by TFF.
The Turkish Fencing Federation is affiliated to the international [[Federation Internationale d'Escrime]] and [[European Fencing Confederation]].
The federation currently has 2500 fencers.<ref>http://www.gazete5.com/haber/eskrim-federasyonu-baskani-muminhan-bilgin-aciklamalari-10-ocak-2011-74704.htm</ref>
