{{Infobox person | name = Yolanthe Sneijder-Cabau | image = Yolanthe Cabau van Kasbergen.jpg | caption = Sneijder-Cabau at the [[Giro d'Italia]] in 2010 | birth_name = Yolanthe Cabau van Kasbergen | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1985|3|19}} | birth_place = [[Ibiza]], [[Spain]] | occupation = Actress, model, television host | years_active = 2004–present | spouse = [[Wesley Sneijder]] (2010–present) }}
'''Yolanthe Sneijder-Cabau''' ({{nee}} '''Cabau van Kasbergen'''; 19 March 1985) is a Spanish-Dutch actress, model and television host.
==Early life== Sneijder-Cabau was born on the Spanish island of [[Ibiza]]. Her father, Xavier Cabau (1954–2007),<ref name="Elsevier">{{cite magazine| first = Fleuriëtte | last = Van de Velde | title = Jan Smit zegt optredens af na dood schoonvader | magazine= [[Elsevier (magazine)|Elsevier]] | date = 3 September 2007 | language = Dutch | url = http://www.elsevier.nl/web/Stijl/Society/137276/Jan-Smit-zegt-optredens-af-na-dood-schoonvader.htm | accessdate = 17 October 2011}}</ref> was Spanish, while her mother, Richarda "Rici" van Kasbergen, is Dutch. Xavier Cabau was a wealthy entrepreneur known as the "King of Ibiza", who owned several discothèques, restaurants, and bars.<ref name="Esquire">{{cite web | title = Voetbalmodel van de dag: Yolanthe | publisher = Esquire.nl | date = 21 June 2011 | language = Dutch | url = http://www.esquire.nl/stijltips/2135/Voetbalmodel-van-de-dag-Yolanthe.aspx | accessdate = 17 October 2011}}</ref> Sneijder-Cabau's childhood in Spain was marked by [[domestic violence]], after her father experienced financial problems and became addicted to drugs.<ref name="AD">{{cite news | title = Yolanthe Sneijder-Cabau: Er was veel angst in mijn jeugd | newspaper = [[Algemeen Dagblad]] | date = 4 October 2011 | language = Dutch | url = http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1002/Showbizz-TV/article/detail/2946763/2011/10/04/Yolanthe-Sneijder-Cabau-Er-was-veel-angst-in-mijn-jeugd.dhtml | accessdate = 17 October 2011}}</ref> When she was five years old, her mother moved with her children to her native Netherlands.<ref name="AD"/> She has seven siblings, as well as five half-siblings from her father's second marriage.<ref name="Elsevier"/> After graduating from high school at the age of 17, Sneijder-Cabau decided to pursue an acting career.<ref name="Esquire"/>
==Career== Sneijder-Cabau appeared in the Dutch productions ''Snowfever'' (2004) and ''Costa!'' (2005). From 2005 to 2008, she had a recurring role in the [[soap opera]] ''Onderweg naar morgen''. In 2006, Sneijder-Cabau starred in the short film ''[[Turkse chick]]'', which was nominated for a [[Gouden Kalf]], the Dutch equivalent of an [[Academy Award]]. A real-life [[WAGs|WAG]], she appeared in the third season of the [[dramedy]] ''[[Voetbalvrouwen]]'', similar to the British series ''[[Footballers' Wives]]''.<ref>{{IMDb name|1597542}}</ref> In 2006, 2007, and 2009, Sneijder-Cabau was voted the "Sexiest Dutch Woman" by the Dutch ''[[FHM]]''.<ref>{{cite web | title = Yolanthe FHM's meest sexy vrouw | publisher = FHM.nl | date = 8 September 2009 | language = Dutch | url = http://www.fhm.nl/meisjes/626/YOLANTHE-FHMS-MEEST-SEXY-VROUW.aspx | accessdate = 17 October 2011}}</ref>
==Personal life== Sneijder-Cabau began a relationship with football player [[Wesley Sneijder]] in 2009. They were married on 17 July 2010 in [[Tuscany]], Italy, six days after Sneijder played the final of the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Dutch World Cup star Wesley Sneijder makes TV presenter Yolanthe a footballer's wife | newspaper = [[Daily Mail]] | date = 18 July 2010 | url = http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/worldnews/article-1295552/Wesley-Sneijder-makes-TV-presenter-Yolanthe-footballers-wife.html | accessdate = 17 October 2011}}</ref> Following her marriage, she changed her surname from Cabau van Kasbergen to Sneijder-Cabau, which she also uses professionally.
Sneijder-Cabau is a co-founder and ambassador of Stop Kindermisbruik, a foundation which aims to put an end to [[child sexual abuse]] in developing countries. Stop Kindermisbruik engages in actions such as freeing child prostitutes, preventing children from becoming child prostitutes, and helping freed children cope with the trauma they endured.<ref>{{cite news | title = Sneijder ambassadeur Stop Kindermisbruik | newspaper = [[Het Parool]] | date = 8 November 2010 | language = Dutch | url = http://www.parool.nl/parool/nl/11/SPORT/article/detail/1046998/2010/11/08/Sneijder-ambassadeur-Stop-Kindermisbruik.dhtml | accessdate = 17 October 2011}}</ref>
